The paper discusses semantic modeling of documents and analytics-based relationships, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of named graphs and the focus on contextualization and prioritization suggest a possible connection to database systems (cs.DB). The application of PageRank and HITS algorithms for relevancy analytics indicates a potential link to machine learning (cs.LG) and social networks (cs.SI).
